Version 1.7.0

Feb-2026, Performance improvements
  - Switch Data storage from row-major to column-major for cache locality
  - Write whole sensor columns per putVars call instead of splitting at NaN gaps
  - Use unordered containers for O(1) sensor name lookups
Feb-2026, New features
  - Add --batch-size option to cap HDF5 metadata memory usage (default 100)
  - Add --compression/-z option to control zlib compression level (default 5)
  - Add INSTALL.sh quick-start build+test+install script
  - Merge mkTwo.py directory-walking into mkOne.py
Feb-2026, Bug fixes
  - Fix --skipFirst off-by-one in NetCDF record writing
  - Fix --skipMission/--keepMission consuming positional arguments
  - Fix NC_ERANGE writing inf to NC_FLOAT variables
  - Fix Data::load() not pruning mData when sensor.read() throws
  - Fix swapped output filename suffix in mkTwo.py (sdb.nc -> sbd.nc)
  - Add fill values for NC_BYTE (-127) and NC_SHORT (-32768) variables
Feb-2026, Build and CI
  - Prevent in-source builds and add build/ to .gitignore
  - Add cross-platform release workflow with binary packages
  - Upgrade codecov-action to v5 with upload token
  - Add concurrency group to release workflow
  - Drop macOS 13 Intel build from release workflow
Feb-2026, Code quality
  - Fix clang-tidy warnings: assignment-in-if-condition, implicit bool
    conversions, uninitialized Sensor members, modernize destructors
  - Re-enable bugprone-assignment-in-if-condition in clang-tidy CI
Feb-2026, Documentation
  - Add fuzz testing, license, C++17, and platform badges to README
  - Document performance notes and batch-size in CLAUDE.md

Version 1.6.7

Feb-2026, Testing infrastructure
  - Add real Slocum glider test data files
  - Add unit testing framework with Catch2
  - Add fuzz testing infrastructure with libFuzzer and KnownBytes target
  - Add performance benchmarks using Catch2
  - Improve integration tests with option and error handling tests
Feb-2026, Code quality
  - Add structured logging with spdlog, strict mode, and -Werror
  - Remove sgMergeNetCDF (dead code)
  - Fix MSVC compiler warnings (size_t conversions, signed/unsigned)
  - Exclude spdlog/fmt from clang-tidy checks
  - Upgrade CLI11 from v2.4.2 to v2.6.1
Feb-2026, Build and CI
  - Add Rocky Linux 9 to CI workflow
  - Expand CI compiler and macOS coverage
  - Fix Cygwin test failures with CR handling and Unix line endings
  - Fix conda defaults channel warning in Windows CI
  - Fix lcov coverage for missing dependency sources
Feb-2026, Documentation
  - Add architecture documentation
  - Add CLAUDE.md project notes
  - Modernize INSTALL.md with CMake best practices
  - Update Cygwin and macOS installation documentation
  - Add code coverage badge to README

Version 1.6.6

Feb-2025, Improve CI/CD workflow
  - Switch to official cygwin/cygwin-install-action for Cygwin builds
  - Add cppcheck static analysis, AddressSanitizer, and CodeQL security scanning
  - Fix ctest integration (enable_testing in top-level, set working directory)
  - Add concurrency to cancel in-progress workflows on new push
Feb-2025, Fix undefined behavior in bit shift operations
  - Fix signed char left shift in PD0.C readUInt16/readUInt32
  - Fix unsequenced is.get() calls in PD0.C maxNumberOfCells
  - Fix signed int8/int16 left shift in PD0.C meld operations
  - Fix signed char left shift in Decompress.C
Feb-2025, Enable POSIX extensions on Cygwin for mkstemp
Feb-2025, Add Windows 11 compatibility
  - Use conda-forge for NetCDF/HDF5 on Windows MSVC
  - Use winsock2.h for byte-order functions
  - Fix binary file handling on Windows

